### Large List Optimization

Windowing (virtualization) renders only visible items plus a buffer, dramatically reducing DOM nodes and improving performance. Combine with React.memo to prevent unnecessary child re-renders, and memoize list item components.

Critical: use stable, unique keys—never index-based keys as they cause incorrect reconciliation when lists change. Consider libraries like react-window or react-virtualized for proven implementations.

```typescript
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';
import { memo } from 'react';

const Row = memo(({ index, style, data }) => (
  <div style={style}>{data[index].name}</div>
));

function VirtualList({ items }) {
  return (
    <FixedSizeList
      height={600}
      itemCount={items.length}
      itemSize={35}
      width="100%"
      itemData={items}
    >
      {Row}
    </FixedSizeList>
  );
}```


**Common interview trap:** Candidates suggest filtering/searching as optimization—it helps but doesn't solve rendering 10k items. Windowing is essential.

